{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, legal frames and innovation should reduce uncertainties, even if one female academic participant in AI Marketing from Europe emphasized: \"Only one thing is certain: uncertainty.",
    "But what's also assured is that organizations will unlock value from AI and encounter challenges in unexpected places.\"",
    "RQ4 asked about trust in AI technology and socio-cultural standards in the ICM process.",
    "Respondents noted that while we are only beginning to understand the impact of AI on society, economy, and culture, fundamental issues such as profit maximization and societal asymmetry remain unchanged.",
    "AI cannot independently alter socio-cultural values and norms but might amplify or repress them, leading to new forms of abuse and violence."
  ]
}